commit.message: Bump to 0.4.2
build: Add targets for split dist archives

build: Clean up test results and logs

Ensure that all *.trs and *.log files are cleaned up by the 'clean'
rule. No clue why automake does not do it itself, but it complains about
them in 'make distclean'.
Move sources into src/ subdirectory
tests: Fix respecting srcdir & builddir
build: Include all test files in 'make dist'
tests: Conditionally enable DMG/ISZ tests with new enough libmirage
tests: ULFO DMG images are actually unsupported
tests: Disable failing DMG tests for now
Update for libmirage-3.0.5 API
tests: add dmg samples (udbz, udco, udzo, ulfo)
tests: add ccd sample
tests: add cso sample
tests: add isz sample

tests: Add ecm sample to tests

Closes: https://github.com/mgorny/mirage2iso/pull/3

tests: Add uif sample

Closes: https://github.com/mgorny/mirage2iso/pull/2

tests: Add gbi sample to tests

Closes: https://github.com/mgorny/mirage2iso/pull/1
tests: Update URL for GitHub move
Bump to 0.4.1
Update tests URI
Remove support for ancient libmirage versions
Update copyright notices

Support both libmirage 3.0.0 and 2.0.0 API

Call sector types "sector types" instead of "modes", following the
new 3.0.0 convention.
Do not use g_type_init() in glib > 2.36
Bump PV to 0.4.
Convert to libmirage 2.0.0 API.

Remove mmap() support.

This is hard to maintain and will become mostly useless with the new
libmirage API.
Fix HAVE_POSIX_FALLOCATE use.
Use pkg-config for glib, and work-around missing gobject dep.
Add missing largefile support.
